From: syzkaller merger hardening patch
Subject: vm/vmimpl: idempotent OutputMerger.Wait + TypedWriter tee dispatch

Two fixes layered on top of the per-vm-debug-streams patch:

Caveat 1 (idempotent Wait):
  Wrap close(merger.Output) in sync.Once so that Multiplex + Close
  (or any other pair of callers) can both call Wait without
  panicking. Latent landmine in device.go's HostFuzzer path if
  anyone ever passes Console!=nil to Multiplex.

Caveat 2b (typed tee dispatch):
  Introduce a TypedWriter interface with WriteTyped(typ, name, p).
  runDecoder type-asserts the tee in NewOutputMerger; when the
  assertion succeeds, each tee write is routed through WriteTyped
  with the source name and OutputType. DebugSink implements
  TypedWriter and prefixes each line with [name] in both file and
  TCP output. Plain io.Writer tees (os.Stdout, bytes.Buffer) fall
  through to the legacy Write path unchanged.

Regression audit: qemu/isolated/adb/vmm/starnix/gvisor/virtualbox/
proxyapp/device.go-legacy all take the plain-Write path (os.Stdout
and *bytes.Buffer do not implement TypedWriter). Only device.go's
-debug-streams path (which passes the DebugSink) gets the new
prefixed behavior.

DebugSink no longer composes io.MultiWriter(file, tcp) in an
internal `w` field. The sink IS the writer: Writer() returns
`d` itself, and Write/WriteTyped fan out to file and broadcaster
in writeBoth.

Tests added:
  merger_test.go: TestOutputMerger_WaitIdempotent,
    TestMerger_DispatchesTypedWriter, TestMerger_PlainWriterStillWorks.
  debugsink_test.go: TestPrefixLines,
    TestDebugSink_WriteTyped_PrefixesEachLine,
    TestDebugSink_UntypedWrite_NoPrefix,
    TestDebugSink_ImplementsTypedWriter.

---

